f:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Jasper is best suited for marketing teams, ad copy, brand voice content, campaigns, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Postwise, meanwhile, shines for Twitter/X threads, LinkedIn posts, social media growth, personal branding, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2021, Jasper describes itself as \"Enterprise AI marketing platform for brand-consistent content.\" Postwise, established in 2022, positions itself as \"AI ghostwriter for Twitter/X and LinkedIn content.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
10:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Jasper** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (8.0 vs 6.0), more features (10 vs 3). However, this does not mean Postwise is a poor choice — far from it. Postwise excels in its own right, particularly for Twitter/X threads and LinkedIn posts.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value 50+ templates for marketing use cases, go with Jasper. If purpose-built for twitter/x and linkedin matters more to you, Postwise is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
